            </ul>
            <h2>Audio stuff</h2>
            <ul>
              <li>
                <strong>On-camera microphone</strong>: <a href="https://amzn.to/4bCrwNB"
                  >Earthworks Icon Pro</a
                >. I absolutely love it. It has the broacast/dynamic qualities of an <a
                  href="https://amzn.to/3FCVaWZ">SM7B</a
                > (which I also own), with the clarity of a high-end condenser microphone.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Off-camera microphone</strong>: <a
                href="https://amzn.to/4433KZ4">Senheiser MKE-600</a
              > is what I rock when you don't see the mic in the frame. It's very hard to beat the price/quality ratio of this microphone, but you need <a href="https://www.betterdevscreencasts.com/posts/preparing-room-for-audio-recordings">good room acoustics</a> to benefit from it.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Audio interface</strong>: I use the <strong>Rodecaster Pro (original)</strong
                >, but would recommend the <a href="https://amzn.to/4ihjTP8">Rodecaster Pro Duo</a> instead
